latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Since everybody here is making Jan Feb videos, I am here writing down my Learning’s & Realisations.
Also, I am just too lazy to browse my Google photos and edit a video🐤

2021 Realisations & Learning’s 

• I am not made for temporary people or temporary things

• I need to get out of the fact that I need to embarrass myself to get over something.

• Invest more. The more I stuff my account with money, The more idle I become.

• Stop getting excited for temporary happiness.

• Procrastination is no good.

2022 is going be about

• HAVE A PROPER WORK LIFE BALANCE.

• Learning one new Yoga pose every month.

• Exercise more.

• TRAVEL MORE.

• Stop procrastinating all the time.

• Have a balance between Netflix & Real life

• Spend more time with people who give a shit about me :)

• Embarrass myself less

• MAKE MORE MONEY🐤 

• Be Consistent with everything I decide to do.

Thanks for reading and Have fun tonight❤️

PS - I am staying home tonight & Pizza, Wine is going to comfort me while I am watching Netflix and working(Yep, It’s a workday today)🐤

latestIgtvVideos.caption:

latestIgtvVideos.title: How to drape a Handloom Cotton Saree
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Long time no see🥺
I think I have to be more consistent on IGTV😷

Draping a handloom saree is a little tricky.. You can finish it off in a minute or you can also take 30mins to adjust that one missing fold or by just trying to clear that messy fold in saree.. Because it’s a handloom cotton..
.
I wore this a few days back to an app preview event in Hyderabad. It also had an after party thing ! 
I was there at a pub in saree asking for cocktails and dancing like a mad chick wearing this😂

You just have to be a little careful while draping.. Once you’re set with it lock it with safety pins and you will be set for that day😄
.
I wore this to an evening party with everything pink(From bindi to clutch).. But you can totally wear this to office by playing around Pallu and accessories💕

In my opinion, One should own both a blow brush & a straightener.

**Blow brush**
Blow brush is for everyone who does their hair almost every week and doesn’t really care about whether it is pin straight or wavy. Blow brush automatically gives you waves in just a day but less heat and less effort and I personally use blow brush almost every time I want to do my hair. 

**Straightener**
While straightener gives you pin straight hair and lasts for more days but a lot of heat and so much effort so I only use this when it is absolutely necessary and important. I sometimes use straightener for front roots along with my blow brush. 
Hence, I need both🫂
.
Straightener - @theagaro_lifestyle 
Blow brush - @makemeebold_official 
.

It’s almost like losing a part of my body, Losing my personality and almost felt like I am giving up. But in reality, I did my everything, I hustled to the very end to keep doing it but it was time, It was time to let it go and see what happenes when I finally take the leap of faith and move on to the next phase of my life, It was time to give my body rest from 10 years of night shifts and give it some peace. I can’t deny how nervous I am to be unemployed and say I am now a full time content creator & entrepreneur. It was the biggest phase of my life and it gave me so many experiences and so much financial freedom to explore life. This stays very dear to my heart. Please keep me in your prayers. Your girl needs to win, Needs to prove her parents that she is made for bigger things❤️‍🩹
.
